sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MutWH as ODH Mutating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ValWH as ODH Validating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant NC as notebook-controller
    participant ODH as odh-notebook-controller
    participant GW as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DSPA as DSPA<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,DSPA: Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Network Exposure

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>MutWH: Admission Review (CREATE)<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS serving cert
    Note right of MutWH: Injects: kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>CA bundles, pipeline secrets,<br/>MLflow env, proxy env,<br/>reconciliation lock annotation
    MutWH-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook

    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook created

    par notebook-controller reconcile
        NC->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        NC->>K8sAPI: Create Service (port 80→8888)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    and odh-notebook-controller reconcile
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute in central namespace<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create kube-rbac-proxy Service (8443)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>DSPA: Read DSPA CR status<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create ds-pipeline-config Secret<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        ODH->>K8sAPI: Create DSPA/MLflow RoleBindings<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
        Note right of ODH: Removes reconciliation lock<br/>annotation → pod starts
    end

    Note over User,DSPA: Flow 2: User Accesses Notebook (with auth)

    User->>GW: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}/*<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW->>RBAC: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS serving cert,<br/>Bearer Token forwarded
    RBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(can user GET notebooks?)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>RBAC: Allowed
    RBAC->>Jupyter: Proxy to notebook<br/>HTTP/8888, localhost<br/>X-Auth-Request-User header
    Jupyter-->>RBAC: Response
    RBAC-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>User: Notebook UI

    Note over User,DSPA: Flow 3: Idle Notebook Culling

    loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD (default 1 min)
        NC->>Jupyter: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/8888, no auth
        Jupyter-->>NC: Kernel states
        NC->>Jupyter: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/8888, no auth
        Jupyter-->>NC: Terminal activity
        alt All kernels idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME
            NC->>K8sAPI: Patch Notebook annotation<br/>kubeflow-resource-stopped<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
            Note right of NC: StatefulSet scaled to 0
        end
    end
